text: Ana de Oliveira Barros (born 5 February 1973) is a road cyclist from Portugal. She represented her nation at the 1996 Summer Olympics in the women's road race. ==References== ==External links== * profile at sports-reference.com Category:Portuguese female cyclists Category:Cyclists at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic cyclists of Portugal Category:Living people Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:1973 births
